OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1782267480
OL,3,CFrustration and disappointment for
OL,4,CEngland fans following 0-0 draw with
OL,5,CGhana
OL,7,FA father and son duo described
OL,8,FEngland's dull 0-0 draw against Ghana
OL,9,Fas an "anti-climax" following their
OL,10,Fstatement 4-2 win against Croatia.
OL,12,FDerek Rogers, 68, from Hertford, said:
OL,13,F"It was an anti-climax but after the
OL,14,FCroatia game it was always going to be
OL,15,Ftough.
OL,17,F"Hats off to Ghana ` they defended
OL,18,Freally well and we were just slow
OL,19,Fagain.
OL,26,@qD@GOUqD@SO]uD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1782267480
OL,3,CFrustration and disappointment for
OL,4,CEngland fans following 0-0 draw with
OL,5,CGhana
OL,7,F"It's not the end of the world at all
OL,8,F` it's just old school World Cup
OL,9,Ffootball."
OL,11,FHis 35-year-old son Elliot, also from
OL,12,FHertford, said: "It took so long for
OL,13,Fthings to happen... so it's
OL,14,Ffrustrating."
OL,16,FMany England fans wore ponchos to the
OL,17,Fgame due to the rain, but that failed
OL,18,Fto dampen their optimism of the Three
OL,19,FLions' chances in their next match
OL,20,Fagainst Panama.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@JO]tD@QOUvD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1782267480
OL,3,CFrustration and disappointment for
OL,4,CEngland fans following 0-0 draw with
OL,5,CGhana
OL,7,F"I think we'll win the group. We're
OL,8,Foptimistic but a little bit
OL,9,Fdisappointed tonight," 66-year-old
OL,10,FMartin Davison from Leatherhead said.
OL,12,FErnie Bennett, who was among a trio of
OL,13,F17-year-olds from Buxton in Derbyshire
OL,14,Fwho dressed as lions, told the Press
OL,15,FAssociation: "It was disappointing to
OL,16,Fcome away with a draw ` should have
OL,17,Ftaken our chances and we would have
OL,18,Fwon it."
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@VO]wD@NOUzD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
